3) Investigate node-5 host-level causes: inspect host CPU load, runaway processes, cgroups limits, noisy neighbors, kernel-level throttling, disk usage and I/O, and system logs (dmesg/syslog) for OOM or I/O errors.
4) If confirmed noisy neighbor or hardware fault, repair/replace node-5 and restore production scheduling.

